episode.name: A Few Good Men
episode.description: Tom Cruise stars as a brash Navy lawyer who's teamed with a gung-ho litigator (Demi Moore) in a politically explosive murder case, defending two Marines accused of killing a fellow soldier

episode.name: Flags of Our Fathers
episode.description: From Academy Award-winning director Clint Eastwood and Academy Award-winner Steven Spielberg, comes the life stories of the six men who raised the flag at The Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in WWII.

VOD.name: Rizzoli & Isles
VOD.description: Boston detective Jane Rizzoli is pulled into a case involving a serial killer. Jane is tough, and medical examiner Maura Isles is methodical and blunt. Rizzoli and Isles are bonded by their dedication to work and their strong friendship.

episodes.name: See One. Do One. Teach One.
episodes.description: Series premiere: Boston detective Jane Rizzoli (ANGIE HARMON) and medical examiner Maura Isles (SASHA ALEXANDER) investigate a murder that mimics the Surgeon, a serial killer.

episodes.name: Boston Strangler Redux
episodes.description: Tensions are high as the squad investigates a possible copycat of the Boston Strangler. Jane butts heads with her new boss, Lieutenant Grant (recurring guest star DONNIE WAHLBERG).

episodes.name: Sympathy for the Devil
episodes.description: Jane and Maura investigate the death of a young Cape Verdean boy who may have died during an attempted exorcism. Plus, Jane's mother sets her up on a surprise date.

episodes.name: She Works Hard For the Money
episodes.description: After a student is gunned down in broad daylight, the investigation reveals she had more than a few secrets. Meanwhile, Jane's mother and father get into a spat.

episodes.name: Money For Nothing
episodes.description: An aristocratic Boston family member is found dead. Maura's ties to the family and Jane's resentment over their wealth threaten the investigation. MARK-PAUL GOSSELAAR guest stars.

episodes.name: I Kissed a Girl
episodes.description: After an apparent hate crime against a woman leaving a lesbian bar, Jane goes undercover. Maura sets up Jane with a hot yoga teacher. ANTONIO SABATO JR. and BRENDA STRONG appear.

episodes.name: Born to Run
episodes.description: The Boston Marathon turns into a crime scene as a shooter targets runners. Jane and Maura must investigate in secret so as not to cause a mass panic. BALTHAZAR GETTY guest stars.

episodes.name: I'm Your Boogie Man
episodes.description: A body found in a park seems to be the work of Hoyt, the imprisoned serial killer who nearly murdered Jane. BILLY BURKE (Twilight) appears as FBI Agent Gabriel Dean.

episodes.name: The Beast In Me
episodes.description: When an identity thief with no apparent identity of his own is found murdered in his car, the investigation leads Jane into a checkered past. CHAZZ PALMINTERI appears as Frank Sr.

episodes.name: When the Gun Goes Bang, Bang, Bang
episodes.description: In the season finale, Jane, Maura and Frankie Jr. are trapped in a fight for survival on their home turf. CHAZZ PALMINTERI and ERIK PALLADINO (ER) guest star.

episodes.name: We Don't Need Another Hero
episodes.description: In the season premiere, after taking a bullet during a siege at the precinct, Jane is honored as a hero -- until disaster strikes. CHRIS VANCE (Burn Notice) guest stars.

episodes.name: Living Proof
episodes.description: Jane and Maura's relaxing day at an outdoor spa is anything but when they discover the murder of a pregnant woman who had been serving as a surrogate mother.

episodes.name: Sailor Man
episodes.description: A girl is found dead during Fleet Week. Frost's dad (ERNIE HUDSON -- Oz), a Navy admiral, arrives, causing tension. Maura goes on a date with Angela's mechanic.

episodes.name: Brown Eyed Girl
episodes.description: When the daughter of a police officer is kidnapped in front of her younger brother, Jane and the team race to find the girl. ANNIE WERSCHING (24) guest stars.

episodes.name: Don't Hate the Player
episodes.description: The coach of a baseball team is found dead, as the team owners and a star player battle for control of the team. Jane's brother Tommy (COLIN EGGLESFIELD) is released from jail.

episodes.name: Rebel Without a Pause
episodes.description: Maura's knowledge of American history becomes important as she and Jane try to solve a killing at a Revolutionary War re-enactment. Maura's mother (JACQUELINE BISSET) visits.

episodes.name: Bloodlines
episodes.description: Jane and the team investigate what appears to be a modern-day witch hunt in Salem. Meanwhile, Frankie's old girlfriend returns to town with a surprise.

episodes.name: My Own Worst Enemy
episodes.description: After a mugging gone wrong, Jane and Maura delve into a family's background. Meanwhile, a romantic and mysterious figure from Maura's past shows up, causing a rift with Jane.

episodes.name: Gone Daddy Gone
episodes.description: The team finds potential mob connections involving Maura's biological father (JOHN DOMAN). Maura spends time with Tommy (COLIN EGGLESFIELD) and Jane evades sensitivity training.

episodes.name: Remember Me
episodes.description: After a young man is killed in a jail bathroom on the eve of his release, serial killer Charles Hoyt (MICHAEL MASSEE) claims to have clues about the murder.

episodes.name: Can I Get a Witness?
episodes.description: The team and Assistant District Attorney Valerie Hudson (ROSELYN SANCHEZ) work to put away a notorious gang member. Television host BILL O'REILLY criticizes the police department.

episodes.name: He Ain't Heavy, He's My Brother
episodes.description: Boston Homicide teams up with the FBI after a robbery, but FBI agent Anna Farrell (guest star TESSA THOMPSON) appears to have a complicated history with Detective Frost.

episodes.name: Seventeen Ain't So Sweet
episodes.description: Jane brings Maura to her high school reunion, but one of her old classmates turns up dead on the football field. Korsak gets a visit from his ex-wife (LOLITA DAVIDOVICH).

episodes.name: Don't Stop Dancing, Girl
episodes.description: The competitive dance world turns deadly when the mother of a star performer is stabbed at a competition. Korsak's stepson is accused of shooting a cop. LOLITA DAVIDOVICH returns.

episodes.name: Burning Down the House
episodes.description: Arson or accident? Plus, FBI Agent Gabriel Dean (BILLY BURKE) hopes to rekindle his relationship with Jane, and JACQUELINE BISSETT appears as Maura's mother, Constance Isles.

episodes.name: What Doesn't Kill You
episodes.description: In the season premiere, Jane and Maura's friendship suffers following the shooting of Maura's biological father (JOHN DOMAN). BILLY BURKE, JACQUELINE BISSET, ED BEGLEY JR. appear.

episodes.name: Dirty Little Secret
episodes.description: Tensions continue to mount between Jane and Maura, causing those close to them to be caught in the middle. Frankie Sr. (CHAZZ PALMINTERI) returns with news that upsets Angela.

episodes.name: This Is How a Heart Breaks
episodes.description: Maura meets a new guy (EDDIE CIBRIAN) in a very unusual way. Jane is filled with mixed emotions when someone from her past returns. CHRIS VANCE appears as Sgt. Major Casey Jones.

episodes.name: Welcome to the Dollhouse
episodes.description: Jane and Maura must find the clues when young female professionals dressed as dolls turn up dead on public transit. Jane also learns more about how Casey (CHRIS VANCE) was injured.

episodes.name: Throwing Down the Gauntlet
episodes.description: Jane looks for how Maura can meet her biological mother, Dr. Hope Davis (SHARON LAWRENCE). A nun from Jane and Frankie Jr.'s past returns. JENNY O'HARA guest stars.

episodes.name: Money Maker
episodes.description: When an affluent man is found murdered, Jane and Maura must figure out if it's related to his company. Angela and Lt. Det. Cavanaugh continue their flirtatious relationship.

episodes.name: Crazy For You
episodes.description: The detectives must piece together partial clues to lead them to the murderer of a husband-and-wife team of psychiatrists. Country singer CRAIG MORGAN guest stars.

episodes.name: Cuts Like a Knife
episodes.description: A bride is killed just before she walks down the aisle, and Jane and Maura are on the case. Plus, Jane has a new neighbor who captures the attention of Angela, Frankie and Frost.

episodes.name: Hometown Glory
episodes.description: A boy band star is murdered. Jane and Frankie, who grew up with the victim, work to solve the case. Plus, will Angela learn the truth about Lydia's (ALEXANDRA HOLDEN) pregnancy?

episodes.name: Melt My Heart to Stone
episodes.description: In the summer finale, when a statue breaks open to reveal a dead woman inside, Jane and Maura must find the killer quickly. Plus, Dennis (EDDIE CIBRIAN) returns for Maura.

episodes.name: Class Action Satisfaction
episodes.description: When a man having breakfast in the Division 1 Café dies from poisoning, Jane and the team must quickly find the source as Angela and Stanley (ALAN RACHINS) come under scrutiny.

episodes.name: Love the Way You Lie
episodes.description: A famous young writer is found dead in an apparent suicide, but Jane and Maura soon discover there's more to the story. Jane discovers Angela is involved in a secret romance.

episodes.name: Virtual Love
episodes.description: The virtual world and the real world collide when a microbrewer is killed. Jane and the team begin to mentor underprivileged teenagers, a move that ends in near disaster.

episodes.name: Under/Over
episodes.description: A former college football player is stabbed during a fundraiser. Frost's mother visits with unexpected news. Lt. Col. Casey Jones (CHRIS VANCE) reveals startling news of his own.

episodes.name: No More Drama In My Life
episodes.description: Dr. Hope Martin (SHARON LAWRENCE) returns to ask Maura for a life-altering favor, and a building collapses, trapping loved ones inside.

episodes.name: We Are Family
episodes.description: In the season premiere, a community parade turns deadly and family tensions and politics arise. A surprise visit from Lt. Col. Casey Jones (CHRIS VANCE) reveals shocking news.

episodes.name: In Over Your Head
episodes.description: Jane is not happy when a former colleague (AMAURY NOLASCO) returns to the Boston Police Department. Maura investigates Hope (SHARON LAWRENCE).

episodes.name: But I Am A Good Girl
episodes.description: Baby TJ's christening turns grim when a body is discovered in the church. Jane almost abuses her power in order to protect her brother Tommy (COLIN EGGLESFIELD).

episodes.name: Killer in High Heels
episodes.description: Maura becomes the key suspect in a homicide case when her date turns up dead -- and Maura can't remember the evening. Jane struggles between protecting her friend and doing her job.

episodes.name: Dance With the Devil
episodes.description: Maura and Jane unravel a shocking secret about Paddy (JOHN DOMAN) and Hope (SHARON LAWRENCE) that affects them all. Korsak opens up about Cavanaugh's tragic past.

episodes.name: Somebody's Watching Me
episodes.description: When a beleaguered Jane spills hot coffee on a stranger, a viral video of Jane's bad day could jeopardize her career. Plus, a puzzling murder case involving a conspiracy theorist.

episodes.name: All For One
episodes.description: A popular high school teacher is killed. The squad works on the case, but Jane is preoccupied with Lt. Martinez's (AMAURY NOLASCO) seeming favoritism towards his own drug unit.

episodes.name: Cold As Ice
episodes.description: Frankie Jr. is brought in to help with a gruesome murder case involving a youth hockey league. Cailin (EMILEE WALLACE) asks to stay with Maura.

episodes.name: No One Mourns the Wicked
episodes.description: Jane and Maura begin a simulation of investigating serial killer Charles Hoyt's murders at a symposium for law enforcement, and come across a horrifying discovery.

episodes.name: Built for Speed
episodes.description: Jane turns to Lt. Martinez (AMAURY NOLASCO) for help in a case she believes may have been an attempt to conceal drug trafficking, but he seems to be thwarting her investigation.

episodes.name: Judge, Jury and Executioner
episodes.description: A mock trial advisor (A'DA ALISON WOOLFOLK) dies during a competition. Meanwhile, Jane is concerned that Angela may be hiding financial issues. DOUG SAVANT also guest stars.

episodes.name: Partners in Crime
episodes.description: Summer finale: Conflicting evidence muddies a case. Maura debates taking in her paroled grandfather (RICHARD HERD). Jane and Casey (CHRIS VANCE) evaluate where things stand.

episodes.name: Tears of a Clown
episodes.description: When a kidnapper who dresses as a clown reemerges after 20+ years, the squad digs for clues from the unsolved abductions of 1988. Jane and Casey (CHRIS VANCE) become more serious.

episodes.name: Just Push Play
episodes.description: A singer/guitar player is brutally and mysteriously stabbed in a bar -- but did the victim have something to hide? Jane's dad (CHAZZ PALMINTERI) returns, and he's got shocking news.

episodes.name: Food For Thought
episodes.description: A food truck chef dies suddenly, prompting many questions. Tommy (COLIN EGGLESFIELD) announces plans that have Angela excited. Maura's birth mother (SHARON LAWRENCE) reaches out.

episodes.name: You're Gonna Miss Me When I'm Gone
episodes.description: Homeland Security steps in when a senator's daughter is murdered. Tommy (COLIN EGGLESFIELD) and Frankie get into a fight. Jane reveals shocking news that could be life-changing.

episodes.name: A New Day
episodes.description: In the season premiere, a jogger's murder takes on more urgency as Jane realizes the motive was theft ... of the woman's baby. Maura and Frankie face the aftermath of their kiss.

episodes.name: ...Goodbye
episodes.description: As the team tries to unravel a bizarre case, they deal with the loss of their close friend and colleague, Detective Barry Frost.

episodes.name: Too Good To Be True
episodes.description: A killer uses online ads to find perfect candidates for murder: men no one notices are missing. Meanwhile, Jane finds that keeping her pregnancy quiet will be a tough assignment.

episodes.name: Doomsday
episodes.description: A man is found murdered inside his supposedly impenetrable doomsday fallout shelter. Jane discovers Korsak is looking into retirement and Frankie is keeping a secret of his own.

episodes.name: The Best Laid Plans
episodes.description: The team investigates the murder of a wealthy woman with terminal cancer. Maura meets a man, but is torn between the doubts of her scientific mind and the instincts of her heart.

episodes.name: Knockout
episodes.description: While Maura is at a convention, Jane needs Susie's (TINA HUANG) help to solve a murder. Korsak is visited by the son of an old friend and forced to deal with unfinished business.

episodes.name: Boston Keltic
episodes.description: The murder of a rare bookseller brings Jane and Maura into the world of Keltic writings and coded confessions. Angela's relationship with Cavanaugh changes pace.

episodes.name: Lost & Found
episodes.description: The team races against time to find a young witness to the contract killing of a woman outside of a nightclub. Jane puts herself in the line of fire.

episodes.name: It Takes A Village
episodes.description: Mummified remains of a woman put the team's investigative skills to the test. Jane works from her hospital room as she seeks to recover from a devastating loss.

episodes.name: Phoenix Rising
episodes.description: The team helps Korsak investigate an old case. Jane refuses to believe that she's not ready to go back on duty and takes untraditional steps to stay involved.

episodes.name: If You Can't Stand The Heat
episodes.description: In the middle of a heat wave, Jane and Maura find a man who died suspiciously in a bathtub full of ice. Angela discovers a spicy tea with unexpected romantic consequences.

episodes.name: Burden of Proof
episodes.description: A notable county prosecutor is arrested for murder, but Jane begins to doubt he did it. Angela "educates" Maura about kids since Maura will meet Jack's (ENVER GJOKAJ) daughter.

episodes.name: Bridge to Tomorrow
episodes.description: Maura is terrified she has lost her best friend after Jane jumps from a bridge to save a prosecutor suspected of murder. The squad renews the search for the real killer.

episodes.name: Foot Loose
episodes.description: When a severed human foot washes up on shore, the squad is called in to identify the victim and track down the murderer. Angela finds she enjoys helping Korsak.

episodes.name: Gumshoe
episodes.description: The squad must join forces on a case with an overeager private investigator. Jane notices Angela spends too much money and asks Maura to teach her mom how to handle her finances.

episodes.name: In Plain View
episodes.description: Jane and the squad team up with another detective who believes he is hunting the same roadside killer. Maura discovers she has had her identity stolen.

episodes.name: Bite Out of Crime
episodes.description: The squad works overtime hunting down a serial killer sniper. Maura befriends a man who is a witness to the crime, who suffers from a mental condition and believes he is a wolf.

episodes.name: Family Matters
episodes.description: When a woman finds her husband has been murdered, the ensuing investigation reveals that the victim may have been living a double life.

episodes.name: The Platform
episodes.description: In the season premiere, when it appears one of the Boston Police Department's own has shot an unarmed man, the team must find the real killer while clearing the detective's name.

episodes.name: Bassholes
episodes.description: Jane and Maura find themselves in the cutthroat, high-stakes world of competitive bass fishing when a leading fisherman is killed. Frankie pays the price after losing a bet.

episodes.name: Deadly Harvest
episodes.description: Jane and Maura are called to an academic research facility for the study of human decomposition when a murder victim is found buried in a shallow grave with the research corpses.

episodes.name: Imitation Game
episodes.description: A murder sends Jane and Maura into the world of art heists and forgery, and forces Jane to tango with an FBI agent who has a keen interest in her case.

episodes.name: Misconduct
episodes.description: The murder of a crime tech sends shockwaves throughout the team. When suspicions arise that the tech had tampered with evidence, Maura is suspended from her position.

episodes.name: Face Value
episodes.description: After a murder, a witness suffers from facial recognition blindness and can't recognize the killer. The Rizzolis prepare for a visit from a scheming cousin.

episodes.name: A Bad Seed Grows
episodes.description: When a 16-year-old girl is murdered and left in a cage, Jane and Maura must overcome the ethical dilemma of a psychiatrist and the stiff opposition of a fussy prosecutor.

episodes.name: Nice To Meet You Dr. Isles
episodes.description: When the jeweler to Boston's "cool and famous" dies, the investigation leads to a member of the Isles family...which leads to a secret Maura has been keeping for much of her life.

episodes.name: Love Taps
episodes.description: The murder of a college student who had 32 girlfriends leads Jane and Maura into a world of app developers, virtual boyfriends and relationships built on lies.

episodes.name: Sister Sister
episodes.description: When a dog trainer is found dead at home, her champion Rottweiler is the prime suspect. Maura has a peculiar interaction with Kent (ADAM SINCLAIR).

episodes.name: Fake It 'Til You Make It
episodes.description: After a body turns up in Boston with links to a murder in Los Angeles, Jane and Maura pack up their sunscreen and hop on a plane. Angela and Korsak plan a double date.
When an old watch is found inside a balloon of cocaine in a dead woman's stomach, figuring out its significance becomes the key to protecting Jane -- and the people she loves.

episodes.name: Hide and Seek
episodes.description: Maura is abducted, and nothing stands in the way of Jane and the team bringing her home. Maura discovers a conspiracy bigger than her kidnapping, with Jane as its ultimate target.

episodes.name: Murderjuana
episodes.description: Jane and Maura work together to solve a case after some puzzling questions are raised. Jane continues her quest to protect Maura and Angela -- but is the price too high?

episodes.name: Scared to Death
episodes.description: A woman is found murdered in a grisly scene reminiscent of a horror movie, leading the team to uncover a frightening "game" in which people pay to experience terror.

episodes.name: East Meets West
episodes.description: Jane and Maura enter the secretive world of an Eastern European gang. When Maura gets a fever, Angela and Kent (ADAM SINCLAIR) prescribe home remedies, with a surprising effect.

episodes.name: Bomb Voyage
episodes.description: The clock is ticking as the team works to solve a murder with explosive consequences. Angela balks when Ron (GREGORY HARRISON) offers to take her on a romantic getaway.

episodes.name: A Shot In The Dark
episodes.description: When a state trooper is killed, the getaway car is traced to the mastermind of the attacks on Jane. The team must now unravel the mastermind's obsession with Jane to keep her safe.

episodes.name: Two Shots: Move Forward
episodes.description: In the aftermath of the shooting at the end of season six, the team must use every tool at their disposal to find the elusive Alice Sands, before Jane's life is destroyed.

episodes.name: Dangerous Curve Ahead
episodes.description: While the entire Boston Police Department searches for Alice Sands, the team investigates a car crash that isn't all it seems. Plus, a new romance blossoms.

episodes.name: Cops Vs. Zombies
episodes.description: The team works on behalf of the dead -- and the undead -- after a murder occurs at a zombie convention.

episodes.name: Post Mortem
episodes.description: An eccentric postal inspector believes a mailman's murder is part of a larger conspiracy. Angela intervenes when Korsak gets Kiki (CHRISTINA CHANG) a bad birthday gift.

episodes.name: Shadow of Doubt
episodes.description: The team enters into a game of cat and mouse with a clever killer determined to get away with the perfect crime.  Plus, Maura reconnects with Hope (SHARON LAWRENCE).

episodes.name: There Be Ghost
episodes.description: Jane & Maura must unravel an old ghost story in order to solve a double murder at a hospital. Angela convinces Frankie to stop avoiding Kent and accept his invitation to a concert.

episodes.name: Dead Weight
episodes.description: Maura proves a bicyclist's bizarre death is actually a murder and helps catch the killer. Meanwhile, Jane's invited to teach a class of FBI recruits at Quantico.

episodes.name: 2M7258 - 100
episodes.description: In the 100th episode of the series, Jane goes undercover in a county jail to uncover details of a double-homicide.

episodes.name: 65 Hours
episodes.description: As Jane is about to testify in a murder trial, she discovers that a key piece of evidence has been stolen. Also, Frankie tries to impress Nina with magic tricks.

episodes.name: For Richer of Poorer
episodes.description: A forensic accountant is gunned down in a park, and Jane discovers that the prime suspect is someone from Maura's past. Jane also makes a life-changing career decision.

episodes.name: Stiffed
episodes.description: A mortician's body is found in a casket at his funeral home and Tommy Rizzoli visits with his son and considers returning to Boston for good. Jane's loved ones react to her news.

episodes.name: Yesterday, Today, Tomorrow
episodes.description: Jane and Maura work to solve two murders. As everyone prepares for the next chapters of their lives, Jane gets a surprise visit and Maura gets upsetting feedback on her novel.

episodes.name: Ocean-Frank
episodes.description: A dead man is found handcuffed to a bed in his own home, and as the "Bon Voyage" party approaches, everyone makes a video to say goodbye.
